race.comment: WITHOUT A DOUBT (2) was appearing for the first time in 16 months last start and did a good job to work home into fifth over 1310m at Lismore. Will take a lot from that run. Gets a soft track today which is the key - both wins have come on wet decks. STAR OF YAMBA (9) returned a good figure in open company over the mile at Taree two runs ago then backed that up with an eye-catcher at Port Macquarie last time. Major player with just 52kgs after the claim. TARA KODA (6) has been settling well back then working home in good style at all four runs this prep, the latest over 1526m at Lismore. Gets to the mile for the first time which looks ideal. HIGHWIRE GIRL (5) broke through for her maiden win eight days ago at this circuit. Steps up in distance which she won't mind. Worth following. TIETAR (1) can improve further after a much better effort last time out at this circuit when second-up.
